claim: Cell- and egg-based flu vaccines have the potential to develop mutations during production, which may reduce their effectiveness.
explanation: A table titled “Adults 18–49 Years of Age, Study 1” comparing Flublok vaccine versus saline placebo. It lists case definitions (e.g., positive cultures with matched strains, any ILI), the number of cases (n), rates (%), vaccine efficacy (%), and 95% confidence intervals for each outcome. The table provides efficacy data for the Flublok vaccine compared to placebo but does not discuss cell- or egg-based vaccine production, mutation development during production, or any impact of such mutations on effectiveness, and therefore does not support the claim. Note: None
